status/finalizer: required /
retain-until-confirmed-delete
requeue: provisioning, updating, terminating
provider states: create CREATING; update
UPDATING; delete DELETING
follow-up: create=read-after-write;
update=read-after-write; delete=confirm-delete
supported drift: definedTags, description,
freeformTags
reject before mutate: force-new fields
compartmentId, name
create-only fields: none
list lookup:
oci_api_platform_api_platform_instances filters
compartmentId, name, id; exact compartmentId
plus name unique match in ACTIVE, CREATING, or
UPDATING; duplicate matches fail
conflicts: none
open gaps: none
Reviewed lifecycle mapping treats CREATING as
provisioning, UPDATING as updating, ACTIVE as
success, and DELETING as terminating; FAILED is
terminal failure without requeue, and DELETED is
a delete-confirmation target.
Pre-create reuse uses exact compartmentId plus
name matching. Generated reuse remains bounded
to reusable lifecycle states and rejects
duplicate exact matches instead of binding an
arbitrary existing instance. The published
runtime intentionally omits lifecycleState from
the list query contract for first
bind-or-create.
Only description, freeformTags, and definedTags
reconcile in place.
ChangeApiPlatformInstanceCompartment remains out
of scope, so compartmentId and name stay
replacement-only drift in the published runtime.
Create and delete responses expose work-request
headers, but the published surface has no
service-local work-request readers.
Generatedruntime records async breadcrumbs when
OCI returns them and relies on lifecycle rereads
plus confirm-delete observation rather than
work-request polling.
The published `ApiPlatformInstance` kind keeps
generated controller and service-manager wiring,
but a package-local runtime hook narrows list
lookup semantics and clears auxiliary
compartment-change operations from the reviewed
runtime contract. The kind has no secret side
effects.
end note
